description.narrative: UNICEF’s upstream engagement contributed to the development of an integrated WASH refugee response plan for the refugee-hosting districts, expected to bring synergy amongst various sector players and reduce the service gap between refugees and host communities. Another notable UNICEF achievement was the development of a national micro-plan for WASH in school, which is expected to help scale up the WASH in school programme across Uganda. Noting that Uganda is a lower income country, UNICEF continued to support service delivery in all thematic areas of WASH, including community water and sanitation, WASH in institutions and the COVID-19 response. | Status:Met | As-of Date:13/01/2021
